docs.snippet: Britain's top share index fell on Friday, dragged down by a sell-off in emerging markets that hit shares of companies exposed to those regions, as investors digested the implications of Donald Trump's victory in the U.S. presidential election....
docs.lead_paragraph: Britain's top share index fell on Friday, dragged down by a sell-off in emerging markets that hit shares of companies exposed to those regions, as investors digested the implications of Donald Trump's victory in the U.S. presidential election.

headline.main: FTSE Falls as EM-Exposed Stocks Weigh
